Experience

Java Developer, AIG
January 2021 - Present

I am currently working as a Java/Springboot Developer on a large scale project team. The team runs of an Agile scrum methodology. My main tasks resolve around the development, maintenance and implementation of new features and services.

Angular/UI UX Developer, AIG
May 2020 – December 2020

I worked as a UI/UX designer with a particular focus around angular for a medium sized remote team. My work was mainly split between two projects. 1: The creation of an automated version control system to assist with the migration from PVCS to GitHub. 2: Developement of Angular Web Applciation to showcase risk scenarios

Database Administrator, AIG
July 2019 – May 2020

I worked as a DBA, managing servers and databases for AIGs EMEA region. I worked aloungside a small team that was split between Dublin and Chennai. My daily tasks were mainly monitoring and maintaining Dev, ST, UAT and Production Sybase, Oracle and MySQL servers. I also worked on migrating stored procedure windows 2008 servers to 2016 servers.


Mentor, Coder Dojo DCU
January 2017 – December 2019

I volunterred at my local CoderDojo located in DCU. I would assist with the teaching of HTML and Web Design to young adults (aged 7 – 17). This class would occur every Saturday morning from 10am to 12pm.


IT Intern, AIG
January 2018 – September 2018

I interned at AIG during my third year of college as a PMO. I was part of a global project that was focused on the migration of Windows 2003 servers to new servers. For this role I managed the decommissioning of the old windows 2003 servers aloung with assisting with the the migration of apps on the older servers.


IT Intern, RVEEH
February 2015 – March 2015

I interned at the Royal Victoria Eye and Ear Hospital in Dublin. I worked on the IT team, maintaing the hospiatls different systems. I was also tasked with tracking and noting operating systems used by all devices to prepare for a future upgrade.
